&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;duplicity /full/path cf+http://&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;UPLOAD_TO_CONTAINER&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;This should take care to upload the backup files to the backup container. It does that incrementally and detect the changes to your file system to upload. There is much more option for duplicity look at the manpage for more info.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
